info.description:
This document describes Goldex Robot [JSON-RPC 2.0](https://www.jsonrpc.org/specification) API in terms of HTTP requests, so:
* method names should be read without a slash, i.e. `POST /foo.bar"` is `foo.bar` method;
* request bodies are treated as [request object params](https://www.jsonrpc.org/specification#request_object);
* default response corresponds to the [response object result](https://www.jsonrpc.org/specification#response_object);
* numeric response code represents [error object code](https://www.jsonrpc.org/specification#error_object);

In addition to standard [JSON-RPC error codes](https://www.jsonrpc.org/specification#error_object), each method defines local 5xx codes that should be handled.
